text: The Periya bush frog or Sanjappa's bush frog (Raorchestes sanjappai) is a frog. It lives in India. Scientists saw it in Periya in the Western Ghat mountains, 750 meters above sea level. Scientists do not know much about this frog. It looks like other frogs in Raorchestes. Like other frogs in Raorchestes, it hatches out of its egg as a small frog and never swims as a tadpole. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Raorchestes sanjappai
